---
import PrivacyPage from '../../components/pages/PrivacyPage.astro';
import { getProfile } from '../../data/profile';

const profile = getProfile('en');
---

<PrivacyPage>
  <p class="text-ink-soft mt-6 text-[15px] leading-relaxed md:text-base">
    This is a personal portfolio site. It's designed to collect as little as possible: <strong
      class="text-ink font-semibold">no cookies, no trackers, no analytics</strong
    > and no form that stores your data. The only thing kept in your browser is your light/dark theme
    preference (in <code class="text-ink">localStorage</code>), which stays on your device and is
    never sent anywhere. Below, transparently, is what happens to data when you visit the site.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-12 space-y-10">
    <section aria-labelledby="p-controller">
      <h2 id="p-controller" class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl">
        Data controller
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
        The data controller is {profile.name}. For any request about your data you can write to
        <a href={`mailto:${profile.email}`} class="text-accent font-medium hover:underline"
          >{profile.email}</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="p-hosting">
      <h2 id="p-hosting" class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl">
        Browsing data and hosting
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
        The site is hosted on <strong class="text-ink font-semibold">Vercel</strong>. Like any web
        server, the hosting infrastructure records technical logs that may include your IP address,
        the date and time of the request, the requested page and browser information. This data is
        used to run and protect the site (for example to limit abuse of the chatbot) and is not used
        to profile you or cross-referenced with other sources. The legal basis is the legitimate
        interest in keeping the service secure and operational.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="p-chatbot">
      <h2 id="p-chatbot" class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl">
        «Ask Matteo» chatbot
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
        The site includes an assistant that answers questions about me. When you type a message, the
        text of your question and the most recent messages of the conversation are sent to <strong
          class="text-ink font-semibold">Google</strong
        > (Google Gemini API) to generate the answer. The request is made from the site's server, so Google
        receives the <em>content</em> of the message but <strong class="text-ink font-semibold"
          >not your IP address</strong
        >. I don't use these messages for any other purpose and I don't link them to your identity.
      </p>
      <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
        The service runs on Google's free tier: under Google's terms, the content sent may be
        retained and used by Google to improve its services, and may be reviewed by human staff. For
        this reason,
        <strong class="text-ink font-semibold"
          >do not enter personal, confidential or sensitive data in the chatbot</strong
        >. Google's processing is governed by its policies:
        <a
          href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/terms"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent font-medium hover:underline">Gemini API terms</a
        >
        and
        <a
          href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-accent font-medium hover:underline">Google privacy policy</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="p-third-parties">
      <h2 id="p-third-parties" class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl">
        Third-party services
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
        Beyond Vercel (hosting) and Google (chatbot), the site loads no third-party resources: fonts
        are hosted directly on the site and there are no external CDNs, pixels or tracking widgets.
        Links to external profiles (GitHub, LinkedIn) lead to services that apply their own privacy
        policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="p-rights">
      <h2 id="p-rights" class="font-display text-ink text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl">Your rights</h2>
      <p class="text-ink-soft mt-3 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
        Under the GDPR you can request access to, rectification or erasure of your data at any time,
        or object to processing, by writing to
        <a href={`mailto:${profile.email}`} class="text-accent font-medium hover:underline"
          >{profile.email}</a
        >. Since the site keeps no user database, in practice the only data attributable to you is
        any technical hosting logs.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <p class="border-line text-ink-mute mt-14 border-t pt-8 text-[13px] leading-relaxed">
    This page may be updated if the tools used by the site change. Significant changes will be noted
    here with the update date.
  </p>
</PrivacyPage>
